ry, France are looking to secure their second-ever Olympic gold medal, having first won at the 1984 Games in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thierry Henry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\"}, {\"begin\": 1232, \"end\": 1238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5357124618015945e-17, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9983576697329128, \"rank\": 0.0016220432894430592, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twice gold medallists Argentina also have a stacked team with Manchester City forward Julian Alvarez and Major League Soccer (MLS) midfield sensation Thiago Almada.\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1373, \"end\": 1382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999993792699, \"rank\": 5.72627851823604e-10, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1413, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9907308684735908, \"rank\"