2043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The participating countries can name a squad of 18 players, including a maximum of three over-age players.\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are also allowed to name four reserve players.\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hungary and Great Britain have won the most gold medals - three each - in men's football at the Olympics while Brazil, Argentina, the former Soviet Union and Uruguay have won two times each.\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2205, \"end\": 2212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 1.9469005308220433e-12, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5564970963403761, \"rank\": 0.7613482084585428, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2316, \"end\": 2322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.998945945865275, \"rank\": 0.0010549682786861593, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2324, \"end\": 2333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999993792699, \"rank\": 5.72627851823604e-10, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\":